h a damp kitchen towel to prevent it from drying out.","For best results, after rolling and cutting, leave pasta to dry for <nobr>1-2 hours<\/nobr> on a floured cloth","To increase quantity, add <nobr>1 extra<\/nobr> egg per added <nobr>100 g flour.<\/nobr> The maximum quantity at any one time is <nobr>500 g flour<\/nobr> and <nobr>5 eggs.<\/nobr> Increase kneading time to <nobr>3 minutes.<\/nobr>","<strong>Green<\/strong> <strong>pasta dough<\/strong>: use basic recipe with added <nobr>100 g flour<\/nobr> and <nobr>70 g spinach<\/nobr> leaves (fresh, clean and dry; or frozen, defrosted and water squeezed out). Place <nobr>300 g flour<\/nobr> and spinach leaves into mixing bowl and mix <nobr><strong>20 sec\/speed 9.<\/strong><\/nobr> Add eggs and oil and knead <nobr><strong>2 min\/.<\/strong><\/nobr>","<strong>Red pasta dough without eggs<\/strong>: instead of <nobr>2 eggs,<\/nobr> use <nobr>100 g tomato<\/nobr> juice and proceed as directed by the recipe."],"basicInfo":["advanced","40m","1h","4 portions"]}